-- в”Ђв”Ђ Alloy в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Alloy (alloy.ai) is a retail and supply chain intelligence platform that unifies point-of-sale, inventory, and distributor data for consumer brands and retailers, powering demand forecasting, out-of-stock prevention, and retail execution.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE(NULL, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2016, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$approx 60 to 70 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Alloy.ai Review 2026: Retail Inventory Intelligence$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Alloy.ai unifies POS and inventory data for consumer brands. See features, demand forecasting tools, pricing model, and who it is built for in 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Alloy, operating at the domain alloy.ai, is a retail and consumer goods analytics company founded in 2016 and headquartered in San Francisco, California. It should not be confused with the identity-verification fintech company also named Alloy at alloy.com; alloy.ai is an entirely separate business focused on retail execution, demand planning, and inventory intelligence for consumer brands, distributors, and retailers. The platform is a cloud-native data layer that ingests point-of-sale (POS), enterprise resource planning (ERP), distributor, and supplier data through more than 850 pre-built connectors, then normalizes that data by mapping SKUs, units, and timeframes so brands can get a single, reconciled view of sell-through and inventory across thousands of retail locations. On top of this unified data foundation, Alloy.ai offers machine-learning-powered demand forecasting at the SKU and store level, claiming accuracy improvements of up to 35 percent when incorporating real-time POS signals, with forecast outputs exportable to enterprise planning systems such as SAP IBP, Blue Yonder, and o9. The platform also provides real-time inventory visibility across more than 20,000 retail store locations, and has more recently added agentic AI capabilities that continuously monitor SKU-level risk (such as stockouts or phantom inventory) and prepare execution-ready recommended actions, like replenishment or reorder emails, for retail execution and sales teams to review and approve rather than requiring manual analysis. Alloy.ai is a private, venture-backed company that has raised a Series A funding round (specific amount not publicly disclosed in available sources) and has previously been recognized as an Inc. 5000 honoree. Employee counts across data providers put the company in the range of roughly 60 to 70 people, indicating a focused, mid-sized team rather than a large enterprise vendor. Its customers are consumer packaged goods (CPG) brands and retailers who need to reconcile fragmented sell-through data from multiple retail partners and distributors into one system of record. As with most B2B enterprise data platforms in this category, Alloy.ai does not publish self-serve pricing; prospective customers must request a custom quote, and pricing is understood to scale with the number of retail connections, SKUs, and data volume involved. Competitors and adjacent tools in this space include other retail analytics and CPG data platforms, as well as broader supply chain planning suites like Blue Yonder and o9, with Alloy.ai's differentiation resting on its breadth of pre-built retail data connectors and its focus on turning fragmented POS data into actionable forecasting and execution workflows.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '74369188-f2a3-4b16-b206-caa1c4b0f7ef';

