-- в”Ђв”Ђ also available in german в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$The website manubes.de belongs to manubes, a cloud-based industrial production management (Industry 4.0) platform built by German software company inray Industriesoftware GmbH, not a WordPress translation plugin; research confirmed no product literally named this exists at this domain.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$custom$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE(NULL, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(1995, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$approx 70 employees (inray Industriesoftware GmbH)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Schenefeld, Germany$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$German$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Manubes (manubes.de) Review 2026: Industry 4.0 Platform$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$manubes.de is manubes, a German cloud platform for industrial production management by inray Industriesoftware. See features, modules, and pricing for 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$This entry covers the website manubes.de, which research shows is not a WordPress plugin adding a 'this content is also available in German' notice. Instead, manubes.de is the site for manubes, a cloud-based industrial production management platform (in the Industry 4.0 or manufacturing execution category) built by inray Industriesoftware GmbH, a German industrial software company founded in 1995 and headquartered in Schenefeld, Germany, with roughly 70 employees. inray has spent decades building software for connectivity, automation, and Industry 4.0 in manufacturing, and manubes is its more recent cloud platform product: it entered a pre-access phase in November 2023 and had its full public launch in 2024, after being described in company communications as the result of years of development. Functionally, manubes lets manufacturers structure, monitor, and manage production data, systems, and processes entirely in the cloud, accessible from a web browser on desktop or mobile devices. Its core toolkit is built around three no-code design tools: a Datamodel Designer for structuring production data, a Page Designer for building custom real-time dashboards and shopfloor displays (including Overall Equipment Effectiveness, or OEE, visualizations), and a Workflow Designer for automating production processes via drag-and-drop logic, without requiring custom coding. The platform connects to both legacy and modern factory equipment and IT systems using industry-standard protocols including OPC UA, MQTT, and REST, and supports automated data capture methods like QR-code and barcode scanning, mobile push notifications for production events, digital work instructions, shift documentation, and an AI-assisted data-preparation and analysis assistant. Its named enterprise customers reportedly include large industrial brands such as TESA, Volkswagen, WAGO, Tetra Pak, and Goodyear, positioning manubes as a serious enterprise manufacturing tool rather than a small utility. No public pricing is listed on the manubes or inray websites; prospective customers are directed to request a free trial or a custom quote, consistent with typical enterprise industrial-software sales motions. Because the task brief for this listing described manubes.de as hosting a WordPress plugin by the same name, and no such plugin could be found on WordPress.org, in inray's product pages, or in general web search, this entry instead documents manubes.de accurately as researched: an Industry 4.0 production management SaaS platform, not a translation or multilingual notice plugin, and readers looking for a German-language WordPress translation tool should look elsewhere.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '74e10c7d-96d5-4264-ba96-cb2433fa5fc8';

