-- в”Ђв”Ђ Alwaysdata в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Alwaysdata is a French web hosting company offering shared and managed cloud hosting for developers, with a permanent free tier and paid plans supporting over 15 programming languages, unlimited sites, and daily backups.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$EUR 5/month (Plus plan, excluding VAT)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2006, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Paris, France$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$French$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Alwaysdata Review 2026: French Developer Web Hosting$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Alwaysdata is a French developer-focused web host with a free tier and paid cloud plans. See pricing, supported languages, and features for 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Alwaysdata is a French web hosting company, operating as Alwaysdata SARL and headquartered at 91 rue du Faubourg Saint Honore in Paris, France. The company has operated since 2006, originally growing out of engineers working on various web technology projects including content management systems and mailing tools, before consolidating in 2012 into a team fully dedicated to building and running the alwaysdata hosting platform, which it now describes as a European cloud aimed at developers, agencies, and organizations that want data hosted within France and the EU. Alwaysdata targets a developer-first audience: its platform supports more than 15 programming languages and runtimes, including PHP, Python, Ruby, Node.js, Java, Go, and Perl, and gives users shell access, multiple database engine options (such as MySQL, PostgreSQL, and MongoDB, commonly offered by developer-focused hosts), and meaningful control over their hosting environment while the underlying infrastructure remains managed by Alwaysdata. The company's pricing follows a freemium model with three tiers. The Free plan is a genuinely permanent, no-cost tier offering 1 GB of SSD storage, 256 MB of RAM, a quarter-core CPU share, three days of backups, custom-domain email, and hosting on an alwaysdata.net subdomain, aimed at hobby projects, students, and evaluation. The Plus plan, described as managed cloud hosting, starts at 5 euros per month (excluding VAT) and scales up to larger configurations offering as much as 500 GB of SSD storage, 8 GB of RAM, 8 CPU cores, and up to 30 days of backups, with unlimited sites, email addresses, and databases under custom domains, aimed at freelancers, agencies, and small to mid-sized businesses running production sites. The Max plan is a dedicated or private-server tier starting at 369 euros per month (excluding VAT), scaling up to 15 TB of SSD storage, up to 2 TB of RAM, and up to 128 CPU cores, aimed at large organizations, public services, and SaaS companies that need guaranteed, dedicated performance rather than a shared or managed-cloud environment. Alwaysdata markets itself specifically toward web agencies managing multiple client sites, public administrations and services requiring French data residency, and companies hosting the infrastructure behind their own SaaS products, positioning it against both budget shared hosts and larger cloud providers by emphasizing transparent pricing (no hidden fees for standard features like database access or additional programming languages), EU-based data centers, and a developer-friendly toolset. The company keeps a small, human-scale team, described in its own materials as 'a human-sized team,' though it does not publish an exact headcount, distinguishing it from large-scale hosting conglomerates while still serving customers ranging from individual developers to large public-sector organizations.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '995aba1d-0e9c-4720-a81a-5336bfae7693';

